Considering I'm kiting wyverns I would estimate Manaskin would have to save about 15mins of med time during its duration to break even (assuming I didn't lose it early due to hits).<br>
Any thoughts? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulordbug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordBug</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 4:51:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Steelskin uses jaspers <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I find myself using Manaskin more and more.  The amount of damage it can take is rather impressive.  The mana regen part is nice, but I barely notice it.<br>
<br>
If you're mainly kiting wyverns, I'd probably stick to Steelskin to save on costs.  The gems you should be getting can cover peridot costs though.  Manaskin's true value becomes apparent in dungeon groups and large raids. <p><BR><BR>
Ebdain Ahriman<BR>
52nd Renegade Nuclear Technician<BR>
Carassed by the touch of fire<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umcdermit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mcdermit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 5:10:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Over it's full duration, Manaskin saves 5 minutes of med time. <p>Zwobu &lt;Trade Foundation&gt; Innoruuk<br><img src="http://patriot.net/~josh/zwobu.jpeg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=bryek>Bryek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 5:55:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> If kiting its a good thing (if you dont get hit).<br>
<br>
In a group grind its not that useful cause you tend to get hit (even if you're noet blasting...wandering mobs will wack you..i think they know you got manaskin up:P).  I always put it up while the cleric is buffing us before we break though...Im sitting at 100% mana..so why not.<br>
<br>
Dragonraids...always up.  Manaskin eating dragon breath is a good thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenaddaranatar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenaddar Anatar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 6:27:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Can't afford peridots when your able to kite wyrens? What do you do with your money? Do you not loot? I have uncommonly gotten more than 5 or 6 plat off just one Wyren. Also gotten as little as 4cps but thats another story. If your not saving or selling the crappy non-int caster gems for your guild they sell for 47pp to a good factioned NPC. Thats 4 peridots right there. <br>
<br>
If you still need money theres lots of Giants out there just brimming with nearly free plats to give you. Find some in Rathe Mountains, Permafrost or OOT (Gornit). You can EASILY get 1000pp in say 6 or 7 hours just hunting them. Too many copper? Go buy a small ton of water from a apprehensive merchant, etc. Gets rid of the coppers fast. Or just destroy them. <br>
<br>
Theres no reason to claim poverty in this game at 40+. Another well overlooked place that drops decent money is Mistmore. Go clean out the 20s and 30s in the first area. You'd be surprised to see how much money they can drop for you at your level. Its easy. Thus, theres nothing stopping you from using manaskin at all. Theres always that one Wyren that simply doesnt root, BoF or Atols and you end up getting beat upon for a while. Happened to me yesterday. Six roots failed one after another. Had I had on steelskin I would have most like been dead. Very rare but it happens. <br>
<br>
On a average day of hunting in CS like that I used to put about 200pp (in coin no less) in the bank a day. Without selling anything but imperfect diamonds. No known use. <br>
<br>
<br>
Ugh!<br>
<br>
 <p>Lenaddar Anatar of Xev
(Lord of Wizardly Gifts from Tolkien) 56th Level Evoker

Chancellor of the Realm
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uberylshadowhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beryl Shadowhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 8:01:05 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.unlv.edu/faculty/engstrom/images/beryl.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Kelset, do the manaskin test and see what you think.  Next time you are out soloing, dump your mana after a kill on shielding spells until really oom, then time how long it takes to med to full.  Then, after your next round of killing, throw a manaskin on and cast shileding to oom again.  Time how long it takes you to get to fm.  Now you'll know what manaskin does for you rather than wondering.  It's not 1 mana/tick. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarundelpajo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Arundel Pajo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 8:12:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Diamondskin is hardly worth the peridot... it's trash.<br>
<br>
Manaskin, on the other hand, is VERY worth the peridot... at least in my opinion... <p><hr>
