 <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Site Pyro</font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 11:30:55 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.graffe.com/graffe_cast.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Many may think I'm an idiot.. but honestly, I rarely use any type of shieldskin.  The reason being is that I don't get hit all that often (my cleric compadre, Keiote, will back me up on that one).  The only time that I will use Manaskin is when I go on a raid somewhere where I know the instances of having to nuke-taunt a mob off the cleric or enchanter will be higher than normal.<br>
<br>
I will also use it if I am going to solo a new mob and I am in that learning process on how to kite that particular mob correctly.  But when I do that (heh.. this is pathetic), I'll drop down to Steelskin.  Call me cheap but I think 12pp is ludicrous for a reagent. =)  Honestly, peridots should drop more commonly on mobs.<br>
<br>
I'm not rich wizard by any means.. I've learned to nuke, sit, med, nuke, sit, med.. quite well.  I leave the looting for the tanks and if any class deserves the coin, it's the clerics.<br>
<br>
The mana regen effect of Manaskin is a bonus, but not much to write home about to consider it worth me to cast upon myself.  But then again.. I rarely have clarity either.  I play very basicly with the tools I'm given. <p><p align="center"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b><font color="#000033">. 
