  . .</font><font color="#660099">.</font><font color="#330066">:</font><font color="#000033">.<br>
  </font></b></font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uororo7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ororo7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 12:47:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://24.7.174.143/files/channeler.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> Wyverns, once you have tested them a few times, are relatively easy.  You should learn how to avoid being hit.  Once you no longer get hot quading, why not keep up manaskin over 2 hours, for that rare time a bulthor or drake gets trained your way?  Death in this game usually comes from other player error (i.e. trains), or from unfortunate external circumstances (LD), or the unknown (wandering mobs).  Manaskin improves your chances of survival...10pp is a small price to pay.<br>
<br>
Now change the situation.  Say you are single pulling Ice Giants.  You hate the wall warp..so you let them get close before you take off and start the kite...or the initial snare failed.  You get tagged now and then, but the ultimate battle has very little to no risk.  Use Steelskin imo, and refresh after every battle you are hit.<br>
<br>
The tough choice imo is the following, and applies to those who use manaskin: say you quad with manaskin up.  Dangerous area...risky, fast mobs.  You won but got tagged a few times.  Now you have NO IDEA how much skin you have left, you only know it is still up.  Do you refresh for 10pp?  Tough call, if you don't refresh you no longer are really using the skin as ultimate protection from external variances...so why use it at all? <p><img src=http://24.7.174.143/files/ororosig.jpg ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uodaend.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OdaenD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 6:34:48 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ashenvendetta.com/odaen/odaen_icon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Manaskin worth it?</span><hr size=1> At raptors, I was a big advocate of diamondskin for quading.  All it takes is for them to bash you once, and with 4 raptors beating on you as you are stunned, it doesn't take long for hitpoints to diminish.  Besides, once you get it down, you rarely get hit at all, thus giving you an emergency buffer, should you come across lag, the occasional raptor stun, etc.  And really, what else does a wizard do with his money?  Not like you can buy too much high end gear with platinum in my experiences.  Now that I have my epic, my plats go to buying peridots for our clerics for guildraids.<br>
Anywhere else, I always used steelskin.  Hell for like 7 gold, you got a few hundred extra hitpoints.<br>
But, do what makes ya feel comfortable...<br>
